I love the idea of this, but there's a lot of things about this, which don't work.

For one, this seems really  out of character with Wondertainment, which I felt could have worked as a different GoI, or just not involved Wondertainment.

Secondly, and this is a pattern I've been noticing with a lot of your recent projects, there's a lot  here, with not a lot to grab the reader early.

While the size and scope of this were impressive, I don't know if it really justified the length.

I appreciate the work that went in to this, and I think the writing was good, but it just didn't grab me in any meaningful way.

I originally downvoted this, but I think I'm gonna change it to a no-vote. This had enough work, and technical accumen that it should definitely not be downvoted, but I can't make it to an upvote.







